Matheus Felipe shared their own High Five: It's been a few weeks working at Parsable. Initially @RoryShevin who would like to thank for making my onboarding process as smooth as possible. Landing in a new project with a few different code bases (4-ish?) at once was a challenge and gave me, since from the start, an incredible overview of the company's architecture.  @MarkNg deserves s hi5 for being patient with my n00b questions about the product and where to find and do things. @VighneshRege for the professionalism and collaboration while I ramp up in my first real project, lots of comments in CRs and questions about process and code style and being open to my desire to make changes. @YanDavidErlich for being readily available to answer questions that are not too clear to the team and providing great context a feature.  @XichiZheng for also being available to help me solve any doubts I might have in general about the company, projects, processes, etc. And @EsteraKorpos for organizing little events in Vancouver office, engaging people together and making the Parsable Culture thrive.

TL;DR version
Thank you all!
